"Loops are how you spawn enemies, process inventory, and handle countdowns. They're essential."

phase2.brokenCode:
using UnityEngine;

public class LoopError : MonoBehaviour
{
    void Start()
    {
        // Infinite loop! No increment condition
        int i = 0;
        while (i < 10)
        {
            Debug.Log("Looping...");
            // i++; // Missing increment!
        }
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Without changing `i`, the condition `i < 10` is always true. The loop never ends.

**The fix:**
```csharp
int i = 0;
while (i < 10)
{
    Debug.Log("Looping...");
    i++;  // тЖР Increment is required!
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check: 'What changes in this loop?' If nothing changes, it's an infinite loop. Unity will freeze. Always test your loops."
